metadata.name: Secunda #109
A Map Of Life #10
metadata.description:
On Wednesday May 4th 2022 at Arroz Estudios (Lisbon), Karen & Dora presented a workshop around their residence theme, "Sou daqui/Não sou daqui" ("I'm from here/I'm not from here").
 
With a dozen artists we have been exploring the sense of feeling like a foreigner in our own country through movement, dance and physical theater.
We especially had discussions over the places that gave us the “least feeling of belonging”, or “the best feeling of belonging”... and we ended up with the very ambitious project of drawing a map of our life in 15 minutes!
This generative token was created as a continuation of the workshop, and is also inspired by the talks with my workshop partner Laura. The "LIVE" mode is a tribute to Karen and Dora as performing artists. 
 
20% of the royalties amount will be transferred to Arroz Estudios’ wallet, and 10% to the minter.
 
The canvas size gets adjusted to the browser window.
Press key [ 1 ] or [ 2 ] or [ 3 ] to redraw with "low" or "medium" or "high" quality resolution (default is “low” quality).
Press [ S ] at any moment to save a screenshot.
Press [ L ] to disable/enable "LIVE" mode (enabled by default).
Press [ P ] to pause/unpause live drawing when in "LIVE" mode.
Press [ Q ] to redraw and save using the best quality (9900x7000 resolution, the file should be around 30 Mo).

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results. Made with p5js only.

metadata.name: rive #87
metadata.description:
Starting with a repeatable system of colors and/or triangles typically seen in geometric abstraction, rive employs generative art to break/split/rive those patterns–and the comfort we find in them–in slight, seemingly unintentional ways.  With each subsequent split, our comfort fades as the artwork is shredded into barely recognizable fragments of a once carefully orchestrated pattern.

Not all rivings are created equal; some are subtle and barely visible while others are acute and violent.  

What holds it together is what breaks it apart.  

created using triangles and p5js

rive
abstractment, 2022

___________________________

Functionality:
Press ‘p’ to save as a png.
Press 0-9 to render at varying degrees of quality. 0 to 9 (highest quality, ~15k x ~15k, depending on the dimensions).  The window background will change colors when completed rendering.
Press ⬆️ (arrow up) to increase pixel density by 0.5.
Press ⬇️ (arrow down) to decrease pixel density by 0.5.

metadata.name: Chaos Culture #554
metadata.description:
"Chaos Culture" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

《西遊記》第一回:「混沌未分天地亂，茫茫渺渺無人見。」

Chaos Culture is the final chapter of this series. There is a legend in the East that before Pan Gu opened up the sky and created the earth, the world was a chaotic place, and no one knew its appearance. And I have always been fascinated by this mythical story since he was a child.

These three works have a father-son relationship, Research > Memory > Culture, with each work re-growing through the remnants of the previous work, depending on its image. From the beginning of the creative coding, I like the concept of recursion the most. Here I experiment with my central thinking through this iterative relationship so that the work is not only the shadow of the artist but also the pulling force of repetition.

"混沌" Chaos in Eastern culture represents the initial state of things. This state is consistent with what we believe in generative art: Anything can happen if different forces are applied. Letting chaos grow out of order and then destroying it, the iterative process, is like my usual dialogue with myself, and maybe it's all just a diary.

Through these three series of works, whether I can eventually find everything in my childhood fantasy, I am not sure yet. The only thing I can be sure of is that I will continue to explore.

- Click the mouse to save an artwork.
- Collectors who own this NFT have the right to print the work.

Artist: Aluan Wang (ileivoivm).
Made with p5js and glsl.

metadata.name: Wandering Line #143
metadata.description:
An agent moves free around a limited 3dimensional space.
It starts drawing a line that changes its color based on a generative process inspired by 6 paintings of Palazuelo (Spanish painter).
The 3d line get then projected on a random plane and converted into a 2d drawing. Keeping perspective and depth.

This is an attempt to create geometrical drawings that are clearly made by a computer but that resembles a hand drawn / sketched painting.

Press "s" or "S" to get a screenshot.

The parameter digital mood is just how the code feels at the time of minting.

Original piece by Ismahelio. Made with p5js. Madrid, 2021.
The digital mood parameter

metadata.name: Mythologic #926
metadata.description:
"Mythologic" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

Mythologic is a project derived from cloud series, Cloud Atlas and Requiem: Cloud on fxhash. In the series, lines and circles are used in an organics movement like Cloud Hands, which is a move of Tai Chi. Practitioners move their hands slowly and smoothly, make circles and rotate with extreme concentrating. In Chinese we said “floating clouds and flowing water” to describe calligraphers’ freely flowing style of writing. Chi is a very important for oriental artists, and for genart as well. In the series, lines and circles start from one position to another, and develop with organic rotations and movements, like practicing Tai Chi on the canvas. 

Mythologic was inspired from “Classic of Mountains and Seas”, also known as Shan Hai Jing, is a Chinese classic text and a compilation of mythic geography and beasts. 

“There is a beast that looks like a fox with nine tails.” 
“Huangbei: it is a beetle with meat like a tadpole, but with a head and a tail” 
“The beast has the body of a fish but the wings of a bird” 

There are many incredible creatures in the text which describe the oriental fantasy. The idea of Mythologic is to present an illustrated handbook with random generated paintings, each one is like a framed badge, to memorize the glorious age. It uses the "cloud hands" technique in every parts of this piece, the center, the circle and the frame. They are all the same algorithm but perform variety with different density and components. Gold, Silver, Copper, Jade and Ruby colors as noble symbol of treasure in Chinese culture. 

This project use p5js. 

Press 'S' to save pictures.

Thanks to the support of Yi-Wen Lin in this project.

metadata.name: Window gratings 2 #85
metadata.description:
<Window gratings 2> combines 2 images in 1950s: The Window gratings in Taiwan and the Kowloon Walled City in Hong Kong.

Based on the previous experience of <Window gratings>, I rewrite all of the code and give it a totally different perspective.

More than 5,000 possible buildings & floors combinations
Tens of unique Window grating styles, balcony, and roof.
12 different color palette of buildings + 6 background.
3 different color mode lead to totally different images.

[keyboard] Press 's' to save PNG in original size

JT

metadata.name: Circles In A Square World #24
metadata.description:
Circles In A Square World, is a play on the saying "being square", usually referring to someone who is more conventional and boring. In the society I grew up in, being square is what people are being pushed towards. A traditional 9 - 5 in a well paying office job the goal. But I believe that in a world where the majority is square, living the circle life is way more fulfilling.

For each square in Circles In A Square World there is a small chance a circle will be drawn instead. The series re-uses the palettes that were discovered in Ode to Color as well. 

To watch the drawing process press 'd'.

To get a higher resolution for printing add ?size=4096 at the end of the URL in the live view (you can use any size you want).

metadata.name: Dynamic generations #161
metadata.description:
A classic cellular automata updates its state with a static rule based on the state of its neighbor.

This collection was created with cellular automata with an extension of that idea. Here the state and the rule are updated based on the state of its neighbor, here the rule changes in every iteration, here the rule is dynamic.

That change moves cellular automata to another level of complexity.

metadata.name: Glomularus #18
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node
